description.narrative: (Liberia): .The Feed the Future (FTF) Liberia Agriculture Development Activity (LADA) activity will use $5.2 M of FY18 Agriculture funds to support interventions that will strengthen Liberia's food security, enhance the capacity of rural households to be resilient to shocks and increase smallholder farmers' incomes, especially women and youth. Specifically, the activity will strengthen the capacity of agro-dealers to provide quality farm inputs and technical assistance to smallholder farmers; and enhance the capacity of aggregators and processors to add value to agricultural products and support market linkages to increase smallholder farmer's income. These interventions will focus on, strengthening linkages between agro-dealers and smallholder farmers groups through farm-based training and extension service delivery; training of smallholder farmers through private sector actors on improved post-harvest handling practices; market information gathering and disseminated to agribusinesses; and strengthening credit requirements and loan facilitation of agribusinesses.The activity will award matching Co-Investment Fund (CIF) grants worth $1 Million and leverage private investment with a target of $2.6 M including $2 M in agriculture loans facilitated by activity assistance. The activity will provide technical assistance to 50 agro-enterprises impacting over 10000 individuals and support the activity's three objectives: (1) Increase private sector investment in agriculture input systems; (2) Increase private sector investment in post-harvest handling, packaging and auxiliary services; and (3) Strengthened facilitation of market information, advocacy and support..
